thread.title: Everett golfer Bob Burton nails career trifecta
thread.title_full: Everett golfer Bob Burton nails career trifecta | The Seattle Times

author: Seattle Times staff
title: Everett golfer Bob Burton nails career trifecta
text:
Bob Burton of Everett held on to win the 29th Washington State Senior Men’s Amateur Championship and Rick Weihe of Bellingham rallied on the back nine of Thursday’s final round to win the eighth Washington State Super Senior Men’s Amateur.
Both championships were held at Canterwood Golf & Country Club in Gig Harbor. 
Burton is the first player to win the Washington State Junior Amateur (1971), the Washington State Amateur (1975) and now the Washington State Senior Amateur. 
“It feels great. It is something I worked hard for, and I feel fortunate to have played at this level for so long,” Burton said.
  Burton finished one shot ahead of Keith Crimp of Ellensburg, Tom Hale of Lakewood and Larry Daniels of Seattle. Crimp and Daniels both bogeyed the 18th hole.
Soccer • Caitlyn Jobanek poked in an 8-yard shot early in the second half, lifting Western Washington to a 1-0 women’s soccer victory over Seattle Pacific at Interbay Stadium. The Falcons (5-2-1) fell for the first time at home and saw their league ledger drop to 1-2-1. Western (8-1) retained its perfect GNAC record (4-0).
Volleyball • Ellie Britt , Shaun Crespi and Hannah Lautenbach all had seven kills but unbeaten Alaska Anchorage beat Seattle Pacific in three games, 25-13, 25-21, 26-24.
• Rachel Roeder had a team-high 13 kills as Western Washington (12-2) won its 12th consecutive match, defeating Montana State-Billings, 25-23, 27-25, 25-17.
From sports-information reports.
